To write an if/then statement in C, you would use the following syntax:

if (condition) {
  // Code to be executed if the condition is true
} else {
  // Code to be executed if the condition is false
}

For example, if you want to check if a variable is greater than 10, you could use the following code:

if (variable > 10) {
  // Code to be executed if the variable is greater than 10
} else {
  // Code to be executed if the variable is not greater than 10
}

If you want to check if a variable is less than 10, you could use the following code:

if (variable < 10) {
  // Code to be executed if the variable is less than 10
} else {
  // Code to be executed if the variable is not less than 10
}

